## Snippet generation

### `snippet(languages, site_name, sdk_name, api_base) -> dict`

Generate runnable code snippets for the current query in one or more languages.
Returns a dict mapping language codes (`"python"`, `"r"`, `"javascript"`) to
formatted source strings.

```python
snips = qb.snippet()
print(snips["python"])
```

---

## Validation

### `validate(field_metadata=None, validation_config=None, synonyms=None) -> list[str]`

Validate the current query against field metadata.  Returns a list of error
strings; an empty list means the query is valid.

Pass `field_metadata` as a dict mapping field names to their metadata objects
(as returned by the API).  If omitted, only structural checks are performed.

```python
errors = qb.validate()
if errors:
    print("\n".join(errors))
```

---

## Utility

### `reset() -> self`

Clear all query filters (taxa, attributes, fields, exclusions) while preserving
the index and execution parameters (`size`, `page`, `sort`, etc.).

```python
qb.set_taxa(["Mammalia"]).add_attribute("genome_size", "exists")
qb.reset()  # back to a bare QueryBuilder("taxon")
```

---

## Combining builders

### `merge(other) -> self`

Merge another `QueryBuilder` into this one.  Lists are extended; scalars are
overwritten only when `other` differs from its default.

### `QueryBuilder.combine(*builders) -> QueryBuilder`

Class method: create a new builder by merging all inputs.

::: {.panel-tabset group="language"}

## Python

```python
id_qb   = QueryBuilder("taxon").set_taxa(["Mammalia"], filter_type="tree")
attr_qb = QueryBuilder("taxon").add_attribute("genome_size", "exists")
size_qb = QueryBuilder("taxon").set_size(50).set_rank("species")

final = QueryBuilder.combine(id_qb, attr_qb, size_qb)
url = final.to_v2_url(api_base="{{ api_base }}", api_version="{{ api_version }}")
```

## R

```r
id_qb   <- query_builder("taxon") |> set_taxa(c("Mammalia"), filter_type = "tree")
attr_qb <- query_builder("taxon") |> add_attribute("genome_size", operator = "exists")

final <- combine_builders(id_qb, attr_qb)
```

:::

---

## Serialisation helpers

`to_query_yaml() -> str` — serialise the query state to YAML.

`to_params_yaml() -> str` — serialise execution parameters to YAML.

`describe(mode="concise") -> str` — English prose summary of the current query.

---

{% if has_feature_index %}
## Positional reports (Oxford / Ribbon / Painting)

Positional reports compare genomic marker positions across one or more assemblies.
They POST to `/v3/positional` and require a **v2 feature index** (see
`feature_index_version` in `/v3/status`).

---

### `positional(report, group_by, assemblies, *, feature_type=None, window_size=None, reorient=True, max_features=10000, cat=None, cat_opts=None, api_base, api_version) -> dict`

Run a positional report.  `report` must be one of `"oxford"`, `"ribbon"`,
`"painting"`, or `"circos"`.

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `report` | str | Sub-type: `"oxford"`, `"ribbon"`, `"painting"`, or `"circos"`. |
| `group_by` | str | Shared marker identifier field (e.g. `"busco_gene"`). |
| `assemblies` | list[str] | Assembly IDs. Oxford needs exactly 2; painting needs 1; ribbon ≥ 2. |
| `feature_type` | str \| None | `primary_type` filter. Defaults to `group_by`. |
| `window_size` | int \| None | Regional binning in bp. `None` = individual positions. |
| `reorient` | bool | Auto-orient comparison sequences (default `True`). |
| `max_features` | int | Hard cap on features fetched (default 10 000). |
| `cat` | str \| None | Category field for colour (e.g. `"busco_status"`). |
| `cat_opts` | str \| None | Category axis options in the standard axis DSL. |

---

### `oxford(group_by, assemblies, *, ...) -> dict`

Convenience wrapper — `positional("oxford", group_by, assemblies, ...)`.
Exactly 2 assemblies required.

::: {.panel-tabset group="language"}

## Python

```python
data = qb.oxford(
    "metazoa_odb10-busco-gene",
    ["GCA_905147045.1", "GCA_902806685.2"],
    window_size=1_000_000,
    api_base="{{ api_base }}",
)
```

## R

```r
data <- qb$oxford(
  "metazoa_odb10-busco-gene",
  c("GCA_905147045.1", "GCA_902806685.2"),
  window_size = 1000000
)
```

## JavaScript

```javascript
const data = await qb.oxford(
  "metazoa_odb10-busco-gene",
  ["GCA_905147045.1", "GCA_902806685.2"],
  { windowSize: 1_000_000 }
);
```

:::

---

### `ribbon(group_by, assemblies, *, ...) -> dict`

Convenience wrapper — `positional("ribbon", group_by, assemblies, ...)`.
Requires ≥ 2 assemblies.

---

### `painting(group_by, assembly, *, ...) -> dict`

Convenience wrapper — `positional("painting", group_by, [assembly], ...)`.
Single assembly only.

---

{% endif %}

## ReportBuilder

`ReportBuilder` constructs the report configuration for `/v3/report` queries.
It is designed to be paired with a `QueryBuilder` via the `report()` method:

::: {.panel-tabset group="language"}

## Python

```python
from {{ sdk_name }}.query import QueryBuilder, ReportBuilder

qb = QueryBuilder("taxon").set_taxa(["Mammalia"], filter_type="tree")
rb = ReportBuilder("histogram").set_x("genome_size").set_rank("species")
data = qb.report(rb, api_base="{{ api_base }}")
```

## R

```r
library({{ r_package_name }})

qb <- query_builder("taxon") |> set_taxa(c("Mammalia"), filter_type = "tree")
rb <- ReportBuilder$new("histogram")$set_x("genome_size")$set_rank("species")
data <- qb$report(rb)
```

## JavaScript

```javascript
import { QueryBuilder, ReportBuilder } from '{{ site_name }}-sdk';

const qb = new QueryBuilder('taxon').setTaxa(['Mammalia'], 'tree');
const rb = new ReportBuilder('histogram').setX('genome_size').setRank('species');
const data = await qb.report(rb);
```

:::

Supported report types: `"histogram"`, `"scatter"`, `"map"`, `"tree"`,
`"countPerRank"`, `"sources"`, `"arc"`.

### Constructor

`ReportBuilder(report_type)` — initialise with one of the report type strings above.

### Axis setters

- `set_x(field, opts="")` — X-axis field (histogram, scatter, arc)
- `set_y(field, opts="")` — Y-axis field or fields (scatter)
- `set_cat(field, opts="")` — Category breakdown field
- `set_query(field)` — Query field (countPerRank)

### Config setters

- `set_rank(rank)` — Taxonomic rank to aggregate at
- `set_ranks(ranks)` — List of ranks (countPerRank)
- `set_fields(fields)` — Additional fields to include in results
- `set_status_filter(value)` — Filter by assembly or sample status
- `set_cat_rank(rank)` — Rank for category label aggregation
- `set_collapse_monotypic(value=True)` — Collapse monotypic nodes (tree)
- `set_preserve_rank(rank)` — Preserve rank when collapsing monotypic (tree)
- `set_count_rank(rank)` — Rank to count descendants at (tree)
- `set_location_field(field)` — Geographic location field (map)
- `set_hex_resolution(resolution)` — Geohash resolution 1–12 (map)
- `set_map_threshold(threshold)` — Max map points before hexbin mode (map)
- `set_scatter_threshold(threshold)` — Max scatter points before binned mode (scatter)

### Arc report setters

- `set_feature(term)` — Numerator filter for arc reports
- `set_reference(term)` — Denominator filter for arc reports
- `set_context(term)` — Context filter (enables arc2 ratio)
- `add_ring(feature_term, reference_term=None, label=None)` — Add a concentric ring to a multi-ring arc report
- `set_arc_ranks(ranks)` — Run the same arc once per taxonomic rank (one ring per rank)
- `set_axis_boundaries(axis_role, boundaries, labels=None)` — Set custom bucket boundaries for an axis
- `set_axis_date_intervals(axis_role, intervals)` — Set calendar-interval buckets for a date axis
- `set_display(value)` — Set display/presentation options (dict or YAML; returned unchanged in response)
- `set_include_plot_spec(value=True)` — Request a fully-resolved `plot_spec` in the response

### `describe() -> str`

Return a short English description of the report configuration, e.g.
`"a histogram of genome size by species rank"`.  Useful for building
human-readable summaries and tooltips.

### `to_report_yaml() -> str`

Serialise the report configuration to YAML.

### `validate(field_metadata=None) -> list[str]`

Validate the report configuration.  Returns a list of error strings (empty = valid).

### `run(query_builder, api_base) -> dict`

Execute this report against the supplied `QueryBuilder`.  Equivalent to
`query_builder.report(self, api_base)`.  If constructed via
`QueryBuilder.from_v2_url()`, the embedded query is used automatically and
`query_builder` may be omitted.
